From 7c07869339eca3e6eb65ca8c188095a000734f1c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Adwait Nayak <adwaitn@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sat, 19 Jul 2025 12:25:22 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP: wifi: ath12k: Add debugfs support for pktlog

-> Support for below debugfs options is added for pktlog:
   1. start : Used to start or stop the pktlog
   2. size : 10MB is the default circular buffer size for
            pktlog dump. "size" option can be used to
            modify/ configure the pktlog dump size.
   3. dump: Circular buffer where packet log is collected.

-> Pktlog decode info support:
Add pktlog enable WMI command for both pktlog full and lite mode.
Handle pktlog decode info WMI event and parse chip info,
software image, pktlog json version

Update the new magic number in pktlog buf header if the above
additional meta data info is added to dat file only if the fw supports.
if not,old magic number and dont add any new meta data info.

-> Add pktlog tx support

Below patch is implemented fully as part of this change:
654-ath12k-Add-pktlog-support-through-debugfs.patch
655-ath12k-Enable-pktlog-decode-info-embed-into-pktlog-d.patch

Signed-off-by: Adwait Nayak <adwaitn@qti.qualcomm.com>
